--- Demonstrative determiner for non-singular?
--- What is the proper translation of "Dogs eat", given that optional
complements seem to be dispreferred?
--- It would be nice to double-check adverb placement.
--- The plural form of dog might in fact be something different.
The grammar doesn't currently really handle the plural form of nouns.
Seems like she just hard coded some.  Most lexical entries insist
that they are singular.


# 1. Dogs sleep  # indefinites appear to be unmarked for number

kàr~nai sunàa-kwaana
dog     3pl.cont-sleep

# 2. Dogs chase cars
kàr~nai sunàa-fàafaràa mootàa
dog    3pl.cont-chase car

# 3. They chase them.
sunàa-fàafaràa su
3pl.cont-chase 3pl.acc

# 4. These dogs sleep.
wad`ànnân kàr~nai sunàa-kwaana
these    dog     3pl.cont-sleep

# 5. Dogs eat.  # No evidence of optional complements in the grammar.
kàr~nai sunàa-ci
dog    3pl.cont-eat

# 6. I can eat glass.
naa-iyà ci gìlâs

# 7. It doesn't hurt me.
bàa yaa-cùutaa ni ba

# 8. The dogs chase cars.
kàr~nai-`n sunàa-fàafaràa mootàa
dog-def  3pl.cont-chase car

# 9. I think that you know that dogs chase cars.
inàa-taunàa     cêwaa kinàa-san    cêwaa kàr~nai sunàa-fàafaràa mootàa
1sg.cont-think  that 2f.cont-know that dog    3pl.cont-chase car

# 10. I ask whether you know that dogs chase cars.
inàa-tàmbayàa koo     kinàa-san    cêwaa kàr~nai sunàa-fàafaràa mootàa
1sg.cont-ask  whether 2f.cont-know that dog    3pl.cont-chase car

# 11. Cats and dogs chase cars.  # mono or poly for NP
kyânwuna dà kàr~nai sunàa-fàafaràa mootàa
dà kyânwuna dà kàr~nai sunàa-fàafaràa mootàa

# 12. Dogs chase cars and cats chase dogs. # asyndeton for S
kàr~nai sunàa-fàafaràa mootàa kyânwuna sunàa-fàafaràa kàr~nai

# 13. Cats chase dogs and sleep. # asyndeton for VP (guessing that we don't repeat subject)
kyânwuna sunàa-fàafaràa kàr~nai sunàa-kwaana

# 14. Do cats chase dogs?
koo kyânwuna sunàa-fàafaràa kàr~nai
kyânwuna sunàa-fàafaràa kàr~nai koo

# 15. Chase the dog!  # There should really be a tone change on the verb.
fàafaraa kàr~e-`n

# 16. Hungry dogs eat.
kàr~nai mààsu-yunwàà sunàa-ci

# 17. Hungry dogs eat quickly.  (Grammar indicates S-attachment)
kàr~nai mààsu-yunwàà sunàa-ci zumbur
